          intro: 'Demand is the quantities consumers are willing and able to buy at different prices, holding other determinants constant. The law of demand produces a downward-sloping curve: a higher own price reduces quantity demanded through substitution and income effects. Supply is the quantities producers are willing and able to sell at different prices. The law of supply usually produces an upward-sloping curve because higher prices make additional production worthwhile. Market curves horizontally sum individual quantities at each price.',
          introZh: '需求是在其他决定因素不变时，消费者在不同价格下愿意且能够购买的数量。需求定律使曲线向下倾斜：商品自身价格上升通过替代效应和收入效应减少需求量。供给是在不同价格下生产者愿意且能够出售的数量。供给定律通常使曲线向上倾斜，因为更高价格使额外生产值得进行。市场曲线是在每个价格下把个人数量横向相加。',
          model: 'A change in the good’s own price causes movement along a curve, never a shift of that same curve. Demand shifts with tastes, income, related-good prices, expectations, and number of buyers. Normal-good demand rises with income; inferior-good demand falls. Substitute prices move demand in the same direction, complement prices in the opposite direction. Supply shifts with input prices, technology, taxes or subsidies, expectations, number of sellers, and natural conditions. Lower production cost shifts supply right; higher cost shifts it left.',
