          skill: 'Use precise vocabulary: price causes a change in quantity demanded or supplied; a nonprice determinant causes a change in demand or supply. For a two-market question, analyze the first market, identify the new price, then carry that price into the related market as a shifter. On a graph, label axes P and Q, curves D and S, and use arrows or numbered curves to show the shift. Never say demand increased when you mean quantity demanded increased.',
